During the holiday season, the First Lady and President Trump extend their warm greetings to Jewish people around the world as they celebrate Hanukkah. They acknowledge the perseverance and faith represented by the candle-lighting tradition that originated over 2,000 years ago. The article emphasizes the strong bond between the United States and Israel and highlights the historic peace deals brokered by the Trump Administration between Israel and Arab countries. The President encourages building on this progress for a brighter future in the Middle East and globally. The First Lady and President Trump wish everyone a joyous celebration and a Happy Hanukkah.